# Pi-hole local DNS for new stacks

When you add a **new root stack** `docker-compose.<name>.yml` (not Odysseus GPU overlays in `odysseus/`), add a matching local DNS name.

## Checklist

1. **`pihole/dns-hosts.conf`** — append one DNS-safe host **label** (one line).
2. **`docker-compose.pihole.yml`** — add a matching line under `FTLCONF_dns_hosts`:
   ```yaml
   ${LAB_HOST_IP} myservice.${PIHOLE_LOCAL_DOMAIN:-network.lan}
   ```
3. **`home/services.json`** — add an entry with `port` (and optional `path`); dashboard probes localhost.
4. **`caddy/proxy.caddy`** — add a site block if you use optional network.lan proxy (`ENABLE_LAN_PROXY=true`).
5. Do **not** add records for internal-only containers (e.g. Immich’s bundled Postgres/Redis).

Naming: prefer the compose stem (`immich`); shorten if needed (`stirling-pdf` → `stirling`). Odysseus sidecars get their own labels (`searxng`, `ntfy`).

User sets **`LAB_HOST_IP`** and **`PIHOLE_LOCAL_DOMAIN`** in `.env.pihole` (from `.env.pihole.example`). Restart Pi-hole after DNS changes: `bash scripts/start.sh pihole`.

See [pihole/LOCAL-DNS.md](../pihole/LOCAL-DNS.md).
